<TITLE> Khaleda welcomes reform proposal: Gayeshwar </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 25 (bdnews24.com) -- BNP chairperson Khaleda Zia has welcomed a reform proposal announced by secretary general Abdul Mannan Bhuiyan to bring changes to the party, a senior leader said Monday. BNP's joint secretary general Gayeshwar Chandra Roy read out a statement, he said he got from Khaleda by phone, to reporters at an office in the city's Purana Paltan. "The BNP chairperson has given me the statement by phone," Roy told reporters. "She (Khaleda) has welcomed the reform proposal," Roy said. "I -- BNP chairperson Khaleda Zia -- welcome the reform proposal placed before party activists and all Bangladeshi expatriates and other people of the country." The BNP has turned into a major political party thanks to a struggle by 68,000 party activists and leaders, Roy said. "The proposal to amend the party constitution must be placed before councilors. In line with the party constitution, a council meeting will make the final decision on the changes," Roy quoted Khaleda as saying. bdnews24.
